5. Repeat the above test with a two-digit year '12' and a one-digit year '1'. In each case, '0's are pre-pended to the year as needed to make it a four-digit year.

6. Issue: The three (or two or one) digit year '123' is parsed to a four-digit year by pre-pending '0' 0123.

*Resolution:*
A validation has been added to the Date and DateTime deserializers which will return a REST exception if the year value does not contain 4 digits.
